<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Expel" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Expel,</orth> to drive out, to banish: <cit><quote>the dire imagination,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 976" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 976</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>remorse,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 76</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>another heat,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.192" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 4, 192</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>inconveniences,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>him thence,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 4.7.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 7, 33</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>sickness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 3.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 1, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this matter in his heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.180" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 1, 180</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the winter's flaw,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.239" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 239</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>sun-expelling</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>